# Card-compatibility puzzle: Pacifism (LEA-class Aura — "can't attack or block").
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   * Enchantment Aura that is attached to a creature (here pre-attached via the
#     `AttachedTo:` puzzle notation, modelling a resolved Pacifism).
#   * Static ability S:Mode$ CantAttack,CantBlock | ValidCard$ Creature.EnchantedBy —
#     a continuous restriction (CR 509.1a) on the enchanted creature.
#   * The "can't attack" half: the enchanted Hill Giant is never declared as an
#     attacker by the AI, so P0 takes no combat damage from it.
#
# The same single static line also grants "can't block"; that half is the
# identical restriction mechanism and is enumerated in the tracking issue. This
# puzzle asserts the attack-restriction half because the heuristic reliably
# *wants* to attack with a 3/3 yet is prevented from doing so — a clean,
# deterministic signal that the static is in force.
#
# Scenario: the opponent (P1) is the active player with a 3/3 Hill Giant
# enchanted by Pacifism. Without Pacifism the AI attacks for 3 every turn
# (verified by removing the Aura). With Pacifism attached, P0's life never
# moves off 20. Verified live (seed 42): the Hill Giant is shown with Pacifism
# attached and is never declared as an attacker; "Life: 20" holds every turn.
#
# Reproduce:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/pacifism_cant_attack_static.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs

[metadata]
Name:Pacifism — enchanted creature can't attack
Goal:Survive
Turns:4
Difficulty:Easy
Description:The opponent's 3/3 Hill Giant is enchanted by Pacifism (pre-attached). Pacifism's CantAttack static stops it from ever attacking, so P0 takes no damage and stays at 20 life. Exercises Aura attachment and the continuous can't-attack restriction.

[state]
turn=2
activeplayer=p1
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0library=Plains;Plains;Plains;Plains;Plains
p0graveyard=
p0battlefield=Plains;Plains
p0exile=

p1life=20
p1hand=
p1library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest
p1graveyard=
p1battlefield=Forest;Forest;Hill Giant|Id:30;Pacifism|Id:31|AttachedTo:30
p1exile=

[assertions]
# Pacifism's can't-attack static holds: the enchanted Hill Giant never connects,
# so P0 takes no combat damage.
life eq 20
# Symmetrically, the opponent is never attacked here either (P0 has no creature),
# so they also remain at 20 — guards against a state-load mishap.
opponent life eq 20
# Pacifism is still on the battlefield, attached, doing its job (not destroyed).
opponent battlefield contains Pacifism
